‘My biggest motivation is being able to create projects to help bring about change and hold doors open for Black women.’ 
- Candice Brathwaite​

We take 5 with author, TV presenter, journalist and influencer Candice Brathwaite who uses her voice to create change and spark conversations. Watch her reflections on building a more compassionate world, what she would tell her younger self and how breaking down barriers lead her to become the woman she knew she was destined to be.

Cheers! 🥂 For the last in our series of festive COS Moments we've partnered with @threesheetslondon, a London based cocktail bar to bring the holiday spirit to you. Choose from 3 recipes to suit your taste, from an Old Fashioned with a twist to the grown-up Cosmo and lastly a light non-alcoholic spritz for everyone to enjoy.​ Please drink responsibly. 

-

Rooibos Old Fashioned
50ml Rooibos infused bourbon,
10ml 2:1 sugar syrup,
2 dashes Aromatic bitters

Stir over ice until chilled and diluted. Strain into a rocks glass over ice and garnish with an orange zest.

For the Rooibos Bourbon infuse 10g good quality rooibos tea into a bottle of bourbon for 30 minutes. Strain through a fine tea strainer and decant back into bourbon bottle.

Cosmo
40ml 40% (or higher abv) vodka,
20ml cranberry cordial

Stir over ice until chilled and diluted. Strain into a chilled martini/coupe/nick + nora glass. Garnish with a flamed orange zest disc.

For the cranberry cordial. Weigh out 500g good quality cranberry cordial and 400g caster sugar. Add 18g citric acid powder and 9g malic acid powder. Stir until all sugar and acid powders are fully dissolved. Next add 30ml orange liqueur and 2.5ml Neroli oil or orange blossom water. Will keep for up to 6 months.

Apple Spritz
25ml Apple Cordial,
5ml Cinnamon Syrup
5ml Verjus/2.5ml apple cider vinegar
Soda top

Add cordial, syrup and verjus/vinegar to a wine glass. Add ice and stir briefly to combine all ingredients. Add a bit more ice and top with soda. Garnish with a thin slice of orange.

For the apple cordial weight out 500g of Bradley apple juice (or any tart apple juice), add 400g caster sugar and add 18g malic acid powder. Stir to properly to dissolve sugar and acid powder and bottle. Will keep for up 3 months.

For the cinnamon syrup add 400g caster sugar, 200g water and 4 cinnamon sticks to a saucepan. Heat on a low heat and stir until the sugar has dissolved. Do not boil the water. Strain through a sieve and bottle. Will keep indefinitely.
